XeniApp : Hotel Development

Created by vaibhav (Unlicensed), last modified by User 71ee3 on Dec 17, 2021

Goals of Product

  1. Provide the best B2B Rates to the travel Agents

  2. Provide a wide range of inventory options

  3. Provide Detailed information like Facilities, Nearby Attractions, Hotel Chain, Hotel Type, Tripadvisor Rating

  4. Ability to book multiple hotels in one checkout

Business Goals

  1. Figure out hotels that give more margins - show them in the top results

  2. Hotelbeds integration to agents as part of marketplace project

  3. Create a Hotel Mapping hotel, single search results from multiple vendors at same time

Search Component

Features

  1. Search Library

  • Ability to search by City - Compulsory

  • Ability to search by Hotel Name - Compulsory

  • Ability to search by Other Locations - Good to Have

2. Checkin - Checkout Dates - Compulsory

3. Rooms

  • Ability to add rooms with passengers - Compulsory

  • Ability to add multiple rooms - Compulsory

  • Ability to add children with age - Compulsory

4. Search CTA - Should get active only when all field are entered

5. View on MAP CTA - Should get active only when search results have appeared

6. Reset - Reset’s the last search

Minimum Room Price / Base Price

Yes

baseRate (inclusive of taxes/fees)

totalRate (including taxes/fees)

taxes

  • baseRate is base price for the duration without taxes/fees

  • totalRate is total price for the duration including taxes/fees

  • Check if the vendor is giving tax separately or if it is included in the price given by the vendor

  • If tax price not included, then display the base price

  • If tax price included, then subtract the tax amount from the final price

Base Price = Final Price - Taxes without any markup

The above price shown should be the base price per night without any taxes and markup.

If the user has searched for multiple nights, the vendor will return the total price, so need to divide the base price by the number of nights and display.

Retail Price

Yes

Calculated Value using baseRate / totalRate

Minimum Room Price + Complusory Taxes + Markup Amount

Markup Amount = (Minimum Room Price + Taxes)*Markup percentage/100

VervoTech API EndPoint

Single Room

POST URL: call endpoint {{hotelId}}/roomsandrates/{{token}} for the selected hotelID and search [availability] not 0 and [occupancies]/numOfAdults/numOfChildren based on the search criteria and return the results.

Multiple Rooms

When searching multiple rooms

POST URL: call endpoint {{hotelId}}/roomsandrates/{{token}} for the selected hotelID and search [availability] not 0 and [occupancies]/numOfAdults/numOfChildren based on the search criteria

Hotelbeds

Checklist

Details

1

Are you using GZIP compression?

2

Are you using the correct workflow?

3

The availability request should not be repeated in the remaining steps to make a reservation (CheckRate and Booking request)

4

As many hotels as possible should be reported in the same call, without exceeding the limit of 2000 hotels per call

5

All rooms requested for a reservation must be reported on the same call.

6

CheckRate call should only be made in case the rate selected is "rateType=RECHECK"

7

It should be informed as most rates as possible at the same call, without exceeding the limit of 10 rates per call.

8

Does your system show all "basic" information?

9

Does your system allow choose number of paxes?

10

Does your system allow indicate number of children?

11

Does your system allow multi-room bookings?

12

Does your system use opaque rates?

13

Does your system use Source market?

14

Does your system use filters?

15

Does your system show Hotelbeds cancellation policies?

16

Does your system show rate comments or contact remarks?

17

Does your system work with Liberate?

18

Does your system send voucher for confirmed bookings?

Hotel information (Does your voucher show it?)
